To run the applicaiton as is, Visual Studio 2019 (or more) is needed.
1-Make sure that the migrations folder is completely empty.

2-Create a new SQL Server database on your machine and hold on to its name.

3-In the appsettings.json file, ConnectionStrings -> DefaultConnection -> Catalog=database_name;

4-Using the integrated Package Manager Consol provided by VS, execute the following commands 
  ->add-migration example-name
  ->update-databse
  
5-Build the application "ctrl+B" or clicking the "generate solution" button.

6-Run the application "ctrl+F5" or set the execution mode to Realse and click the start button. 
